<div style="background:#161b22;border:1px solid #30363d;border-radius:6px;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;max-width:700px;margin:2rem auto;text-align:center">
<p style="color:#f0f6fc;font-weight:600;font-size:1rem;margin:0 0 0.5rem">State Bankruptcy Guides</p>
<p style="color:#9eaab6;font-size:0.88rem;margin:0 0 0.75rem">Exemptions vary dramatically by state. Find your state's homestead, vehicle, and wildcard exemptions.</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 0.75rem;font-size:0.85rem;line-height:1.8"><a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/california.html" style="color:#58a6ff;white-space:nowrap">California</a> <span style="color:#30363d">·</span> <a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/texas.html" style="color:#58a6ff;white-space:nowrap">Texas</a> <span style="color:#30363d">·</span> <a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/florida.html" style="color:#58a6ff;white-space:nowrap">Florida</a> <span style="color:#30363d">·</span> <a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/new-york.html" style="color:#58a6ff;white-space:nowrap">New York</a> <span style="color:#30363d">·</span> <a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/illinois.html" style="color:#58a6ff;white-space:nowrap">Illinois</a> <span style="color:#30363d">·</span> <a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/ohio.html" style="color:#58a6ff;white-space:nowrap">Ohio</a></p>
<a href="https://bankruptcyexemptionsbystate.com/states/" style="display:inline-block;background:#238636;color:#fff;padding:0.45rem 1.25rem;border-radius:6px;font-weight:600;font-size:0.88rem;text-decoration:none">Browse All 50 State Guides →</a>
</div>
